Sasol Sells Two of Five Fertilizer Plants Under Deal, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-18T05:18:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/sasol-sells-two-of-five-fertilizer-plants-under-deal-business-day-reports.html
Sasol Ltd. (SOL)  has sold two of the five
fertilizer plants it agreed to dispose of as part of an
antitrust settlement agreement, Business Day reported, citing
Cobus Jansen, a brand manager at Sasol Infrachem.  Sasol sold its operations in Potchefstroom and Durban and
now plans to dispose of its plants at Kimberley, Endicott and
Bellville, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  The value of the agreement for the two plants that have
been sold so far wasnâ€™t disclosed, Business Day said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
